# Implementation Plan - Single Screen & Stats Update

## Goal Description
Refactor the application to use a single-screen layout (SPA without route transitions) where Dashboard, Stats, and Profile are accessed via a persistent bottom navigation bar. Additionally, enable habit completion toggling directly from the Stats page's "Total Status" section.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> This refactor removes `react-router-dom` for the main navigation. URL routing (e.g., `/stats`, `/habit/1`) will no longer work directly by entering the URL. The app will behave like a native mobile app with internal state.

## Proposed Changes

### Logic & State Management
#### [MODIFY] [App.jsx](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/매일%20습관/daily-habit-tracker/src/App.jsx)
- Remove `<Router>`, `<Routes>`, `<Route>` components.
- ADD `currentView` state (default: `'dashboard'`).
- ADD `selectedHabitId` state (default: `null`).
- Create `renderView()` function to conditionally display [Dashboard](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EB%A7%A4%EC%9D%BC%20%EC%8A%B5%EA%B4%80/daily-habit-tracker/src/Dashboard.jsx#7-130), [Stats](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EB%A7%A4%EC%9D%BC%20%EC%8A%B5%EA%B4%80/daily-habit-tracker/src/Stats.jsx#4-68), or [Profile](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EB%A7%A4%EC%9D%BC%20%EC%8A%B5%EA%B4%80/daily-habit-tracker/src/Profile.jsx#5-299).
- Implement [Navigation](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EB%A7%A4%EC%9D%BC%20%EC%8A%B5%EA%B4%80/daily-habit-tracker/src/Navigation.jsx#3-30) component outside the specific views to make it persistent (if styling allows) or pass props down. *Decision*: Keep Navigation inside components for safest styling, but pass `currentView`/`setCurrentView` props. Or better: Move Navigation to [App.jsx](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EB%A7%A4%EC%9D%BC%20%EC%8A%B5%EA%B4%80/daily-habit-tracker/src/App.jsx) to ensure it doesn't re-render/flash.
- Pass [toggleHabit](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EB%A7%A4%EC%9D%BC%20%EC%8A%B5%EA%B4%80/daily-habit-tracker/src/App.jsx#105-121) to [Stats](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EB%A7%A4%EC%9D%BC%20%EC%8A%B5%EA%B4%80/daily-habit-tracker/src/Stats.jsx#4-68) component.

### Components
#### [MODIFY] [Navigation.jsx](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/매일%20습관/daily-habit-tracker/src/Navigation.jsx)
- Remove `useNavigate`, `useLocation`.
- Accept `currentView`, `onViewChange` props.
- Update buttons to call `onViewChange`.

#### [MODIFY] [Dashboard.jsx](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/매일%20습관/daily-habit-tracker/src/Dashboard.jsx)
- Remove internal `<Navigation />`.
- Update `navigate` calls to use `onOpenHabit(id)` prop passed from [App.jsx](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EB%A7%A4%EC%9D%BC%20%EC%8A%B5%EA%B4%80/daily-habit-tracker/src/App.jsx).

#### [MODIFY] [Stats.jsx](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/매일%20습관/daily-habit-tracker/src/Stats.jsx)
- Remove internal `<Navigation />`.
- Accept [toggleHabit](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EB%A7%A4%EC%9D%BC%20%EC%8A%B5%EA%B4%80/daily-habit-tracker/src/App.jsx#105-121) prop.
- Update "Total Status" list items to be clickable/interactive to toggle habits.

#### [MODIFY] [Profile.jsx](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/매일%20습관/daily-habit-tracker/src/Profile.jsx)
- Remove internal `<Navigation />`.
- Remove `useNavigate` if used.

#### [MODIFY] [HabitDetail.jsx](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/매일%20습관/daily-habit-tracker/src/HabitDetail.jsx)
- Remove `useParams`, `useNavigate`.
- Accept `habitId` (or `habit` object) and `onClose` props.
- Update "Back" buttons to call `onClose`.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- None (Visual/Interaction changes).

### Manual Verification
1. **Layout Check**:
   - Run `npm run dev`.
   - Open localhost.
   - Verify that switching tabs (Home -> Stats -> Profile) is instant and feels like "one screen".
   - Verify [HabitDetail](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EB%A7%A4%EC%9D%BC%20%EC%8A%B5%EA%B4%80/daily-habit-tracker/src/HabitDetail.jsx#5-135) opens as an overlay/view replacement and "Back" returns to the previous state correctly.
2. **Stats Functionality**:
   - Go to Stats page.
   - Check the "Total Status" count for a habit (e.g., "5회").
   - Click the habit in the list.
   - Verify the count increments (or decrements if toggled off) immediately.
   - Go back to Dashboard and verify the habit is checked there too.
